This paper deals with communication systems and interference channels, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the practical implementation of the proposed scheme, which falls under the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper compares the proposed scheme with existing cellular communication systems, which is related to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
